# Component Development Rules

## Versioning
- Always increment version numbers in new files
- Archive old versions in Archive/ subdirectory
- Update PROJECT_NOTES.md component registry (auto-updates via git hooks)

## Documentation
- Update MASTER.md when adding significant features
- Use claude-export to integrate session notes
- Reference Data_analysis_MASTER.md for data insights

## Code Style
- Monolithic components for Framer compatibility
- TypeScript strict mode
- Framer Motion for animations
- Accessibility first (WCAG 2.1 AA)

## Component Structure
- Latest version in component root directory
- Archive older versions in Archive/ subdirectory
- Use naming: ComponentName.X.Y.Z.tsx

## Git Commit Format
- Use format: [Component] Description
- Examples:
  - [Carousel] Fixed glide distance in 2-column mode
  - [ThumbReachMapper] Added new calibration step
  - [Docs] Updated API reference
  - [Scripts] Added release notes generator

## Testing
- Run tests before committing: npm test
- Update tests when adding features
- Maintain 93.25%+ gesture detection accuracy for Carousel

## File Organization
- Components in src/components/[componentname]/
- Documentation in notes/claude-sessions/[ComponentName]/
- Data analysis in Data/Data_analysis_MASTER.md
- Scripts in scripts/

## Claude Integration
- Always check PROJECT_NOTES.md for latest component versions
- Load MASTER.md files for comprehensive context
- Reference Data_analysis_MASTER.md for data-driven insights
- Use claude-export after session to integrate notes

